        <headline>Flood Advisory issued June 27 at 5:15PM EDT until June 27 at 8:15PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Urban and small stream flooding caused by excessive
rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...Portions of south central and southwest Michigan,
including the following counties, in south central Michigan,
Calhoun. In southwest Michigan, Kalamazoo.

* WHEN...Until 815 PM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
Water over roadways.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 514 PM EDT, Radar and automated rain gauges indicate 1 to
2 inches of rain has fallen with another 0.5 to 1.0 inches of
rain expected over the next hour or so. This will cause urban
and small stream flooding.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Marshall, Battle Creek, Climax, Brownlee Park, Ceresco and
Pine Creek.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
